Sentencas: A quasi-three-dimensional solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) model reduces the computational cost by strategically ignoring the thinnest direction in an SOFC by incorporating a charge -transfer current density model to represent its active thickness in electrodes to represent its complex phenomenon in an electrode.
Titulo: Numerical analysis on the anode active thickness using quasi-three-dimensional solid oxide fuel cell model

Sentencas: Therefore, high accuracy of this charge-transfer current density model is required.
Titulo: Numerical analysis on the anode active thickness using quasi-three-dimensional solid oxide fuel cell model

Sentencas: The concentration loss is mathematically related to the charge-transfer current density based on the dusty-gas model together with activation and ohmic losses in this work.
Titulo: Numerical analysis on the anode active thickness using quasi-three-dimensional solid oxide fuel cell model

Sentencas: The numerical results from this study are validated with the experimental results.
Titulo: Numerical analysis on the anode active thickness using quasi-three-dimensional solid oxide fuel cell model

Sentencas: The influence of anode's thickness towards anode active thickness is studied with the anode thickness of 5, 10, 50, 100, 500 and 1000 mm.
